Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua has set up camp in Kitui county this week to popularise his Maendeleo Chap Chap party.On Monday, he declared he will support President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s reelection bid. Mutua said his party will field candidates for all other posts.&ldquo;The support I am receiving from aspirants is overwhelming,&rdquo; he said. Mutua assured aspirants they will receive financial support. He will visit all six subcounties in Kitui. Mutua held a question and answer forum with residents and leaders of Ikutha ward and was hosted by Narc MCA Hussein Mwandia. He said, &ldquo;I have shared my personal story of growing up in a poor city slum. This story is no different from that of many children growing up in rural Kenya. I want to transform the county.&rdquo;Mutua said it is deplorable some residents still lack clean drinking water, have poor health systems and bad roads.&ldquo;We need to change the way we do things. We must pursue goals that will increase food production for domestic us, and improve the quality of education,&rdquo; he said.